<h3>4. Broken Link Building</h3>
<p>Find broken links on relevant sites. Create content that replaces the dead resource. Contact the site owner and suggest your page as the replacement. This works because you are helping the webmaster fix a problem, not asking for a favor.</p>
<p>Our <a href="/blog/broken-link-building/">broken link building guide</a> covers the full process including tools, outreach templates, and success rate benchmarks.</p>
<h3>5. Resource Page Link Building</h3>
<p>Resource pages are curated lists of helpful links on a specific topic. If your content fits a resource page's theme, contact the curator and suggest your page. Success rates for <a href="/blog/resource-page-link-building/">resource page outreach</a> range from 5 to 15%, which is higher than cold email pitches.</p>
<h3>6. HARO and Journalist Queries</h3>
<p>Help a Reporter Out (now Connectively) connects experts with journalists who need sources. Respond to relevant queries with expert commentary. If published, you earn a backlink from a high-authority news outlet.</p>
<p>Our <a href="/blog/haro-link-building/">HARO link building guide</a> shows how to craft responses that get selected.</p>
<h3>7. Brand Mentions and Unlinked Mentions</h3>
<p>80.9% of SEO professionals believe unlinked brand mentions affect rankings. Google's patents reference brand mentions as a trust signal, even without a hyperlink.</p>
<p><strong>Two strategies here:</strong>
- Monitor for unlinked mentions of your brand and request a link
- Build brand awareness that generates mentions naturally (PR, speaking, partnerships)</p>
<p>Tools like Ahrefs, Semrush, and Google Alerts can track brand mentions across the web.</p>
<h3>8. Local SEO Citations</h3>
<p>For local businesses, citations (mentions of your business name, address, and phone number on directories) are a core off-page signal. Consistent NAP data across Google Business Profile, Yelp, industry directories, and local sites builds local authority.</p>
<p>Read our <a href="/blog/link-building-for-local-seo/">link building for local SEO guide</a> for the directory strategy and citation building process.</p>
<h3>9. Community and Forum Participation</h3>
<p>Reddit now ranks prominently in Google search results following the $60 million Google-Reddit licensing deal. Active, genuine participation in relevant subreddits, Quora, and industry forums builds visibility and can earn referral traffic and indirect SEO benefits.</p>
<p>The key word is "genuine." Spamming links in forums is a fast path to account bans and zero SEO benefit. Add value first. Link only when your content directly answers the question.</p>
<h3>10. Social Media Amplification</h3>
<p>Social signals are not a direct Google ranking factor. Google has confirmed this repeatedly. But social media amplifies content distribution, which indirectly earns links and brand mentions.</p>
<p>A blog post shared across LinkedIn, X, and industry communities reaches audiences who may link to it from their own sites. Social amplification is the bridge between publishing content and earning off-page signals from it.</p>
